The Rotterdam Study is a prospective cohort study ongoing since 1990 in the city 
of Rotterdam in The Netherlands. The study targets cardiovascular, endocrine, 
hepatic, neurological, ophthalmic, psychiatric, dermatological, 
otolaryngological, locomotor, and respiratory diseases. As of 2008, 14,926 
subjects aged 45 years or over comprise the Rotterdam Study cohort. The findings 
of the Rotterdam Study have been presented in over 1200 research articles and 
reports (see www.erasmus-epidemiology.nl/rotterdamstudy ). This article gives 
the rationale of the study and its design. It also presents a summary of the 
major findings and an update of the objectives and methods.

